-- IMPORT REST CLIENT FROM OPENAPI — syntax check examples
-- These statements check parser correctness only.
-- At runtime, a real spec file path and project connection are required.

-- Preview an OpenAPI spec as MDL (no project needed at syntax-check time):
-- DESCRIBE OPENAPI FILE '/path/to/openapi.json';

-- Import a consumed REST service from an OpenAPI 3.0 JSON spec:
-- IMPORT REST CLIENT Integrations.YourAPI FROM OPENAPI '/specs/openapi.json';

-- Idempotent variant — replaces an existing service with the same name:
-- IMPORT OR REPLACE REST CLIENT Integrations.YourAPI FROM OPENAPI '/specs/openapi.json';
